WEBVTT

00:02.377 --> 00:03.710
<i>Kids, it was two days</i>

00:03.711 --> 00:05.328
<i>before Barney</i>
<i>and Robin's wedding,</i>

00:05.330 --> 00:07.780
<i>and everything was going off</i>
<i>without a hitch.</i>

00:07.782 --> 00:08.981
Ah.

00:08.983 --> 00:10.433
Been waiting for the
perfect time for this,

00:10.435 --> 00:12.001
and, my friend,
that time is...

00:12.003 --> 00:14.453
I saw you and Robin
at the carousel.

00:14.455 --> 00:17.673
<i>Okay, there was</i>
<i>one slight hitch.</i>

00:17.675 --> 00:20.059
<i>She called me to help her,</i>

00:20.061 --> 00:21.444
<i>and there you were</i>

00:21.446 --> 00:22.645
<i>in the rain</i>

00:22.647 --> 00:24.580
<i>holding hands with my fiancée.</i>

00:28.519 --> 00:29.736
What up?

00:29.738 --> 00:31.303
Nothing up.

00:31.305 --> 00:32.271
Everything down.

00:32.273 --> 00:34.440
All parts of me down.

00:34.442 --> 00:35.474
Look,

00:35.476 --> 00:37.860
you were busy,
so I-I...

00:37.862 --> 00:39.028
I went to the park
to help her look

00:39.030 --> 00:40.446
for this locket
she buried years ago.

00:40.448 --> 00:42.148
She couldn't find it,
she got upset,

00:42.150 --> 00:44.250
I held her hand. End of story.

00:47.204 --> 00:49.122
Cool! I just wanted
to air that out.

00:49.124 --> 00:50.706
You know, bro to bro.

00:50.708 --> 00:52.508
You're my best friend
and my best man.

00:52.510 --> 00:53.726
Of course I trust you.

00:53.728 --> 00:55.094
Oh, come on.

00:55.096 --> 00:57.263
You don't have to cry about it.

00:57.265 --> 00:59.932
It's not that.

00:59.934 --> 01:03.302
That was a $600 bottle
of scotch.

01:03.304 --> 01:06.105
Oh, my God.

01:08.193 --> 01:12.145
I hope Marshall gets here
for the rehearsal dinner.

01:12.147 --> 01:13.362
Thank you, Linus.

01:13.364 --> 01:16.482
He's somewhere in Wisconsin
in a rental car.

01:16.484 --> 01:18.117
Hertz?
I mean, it hurts a little

01:18.119 --> 01:20.403
but I'm not gonna
cry about it. Hey!

01:20.405 --> 01:22.538
We've been doing that
all afternoon.

01:22.540 --> 01:23.873
Oh, who's that for?

01:23.875 --> 01:25.458
Marshpillow.

01:25.460 --> 01:28.194
<i>Kids, as you may recall,</i>
<i>whenever Marshall left town</i>

01:28.196 --> 01:29.328
<i>for a few days,</i>

01:29.330 --> 01:31.447
<i>Lily would compensate</i>
<i>with a body pillow</i>

01:31.449 --> 01:33.966
<i>she dressed up</i>
<i>and named Marshpillow.</i>

01:33.968 --> 01:35.568
<i>Pretty normal stuff.</i>

01:35.570 --> 01:37.887
<i>But with Marshall stuck driving</i>
<i>across the country,</i>

01:37.889 --> 01:39.922
<i>Lily decided to upgrade.</i>

01:39.924 --> 01:43.309
Meet Marshpillow 2.0!

01:43.311 --> 01:44.811
Hey!

01:44.813 --> 01:46.679
Am I on?

01:46.681 --> 01:48.714
Hey, guys!

01:48.716 --> 01:49.999
Hey, Marsh.
Hey, Marshall. Hey.

01:50.001 --> 01:50.766
It's like you're
really here.

01:50.768 --> 01:52.068
Hey, Ted.

01:52.070 --> 01:55.271
Can you give me a
gander of the environs?

01:56.557 --> 01:58.274
Wow!

01:58.276 --> 02:02.395
This place
looks beautif...

02:03.730 --> 02:05.131
Wait for it.

02:05.133 --> 02:07.416
He's frozen.

02:07.418 --> 02:10.502
Same thing happened last night
at the worst possible time.

02:10.505 --> 02:14.674
I had just gotten on all fours
and taken off my panti...

02:19.112 --> 02:20.796
Now Lily's frozen.

02:22.132 --> 02:26.132
