02:26.157 --> 02:31.157
== sync, corrected by <font color=#00FF00>elderman</font> ==
<font color=#00FFFF>@elder_man</font>

02:36.480 --> 02:38.430
...ful.

02:38.432 --> 02:40.900
This place
is beautiful!

02:40.902 --> 02:43.236
Wow. Lily, it looks
like you really put

02:43.238 --> 02:45.071
some time
into this, huh?

02:45.907 --> 02:47.406
Though I wonder if

02:47.408 --> 02:48.774
instead of dressing up

02:48.776 --> 02:52.044
your giant husband doll
like Malibu Ken,

02:52.046 --> 02:53.546
you could've spent
a minute or two--

02:53.548 --> 02:55.014
I don't know--

02:55.016 --> 02:57.717
planning the weak ass
bachelorette party you threw me?

03:02.923 --> 03:07.376
I-It's possible I forgot
to send out the Evite.

03:08.345 --> 03:09.478
Robin!

03:09.480 --> 03:11.814
Happy bachelorette party!

03:11.816 --> 03:15.184
You invited Patrice
to my bachelorette party?!

03:15.186 --> 03:17.136
No.

03:17.138 --> 03:18.404
You know, it's funny.

03:18.406 --> 03:21.123
When I was planning
Barney's bachelor party,

03:21.125 --> 03:25.278
<i>I managed to wrangle</i>
<i>his boyhood hero, Billy Zabka,</i>

03:25.280 --> 03:26.946
<i>from</i> The Karate Kid.

03:26.948 --> 03:28.864
But you scored Patrice.

03:28.866 --> 03:30.333
I'm sorry, Robin.

03:30.335 --> 03:34.453
I-I've just been so consumed
with our move to Rome.

03:34.455 --> 03:36.222
I guess I forgot
to invite

03:36.224 --> 03:37.506
the girls.

03:37.508 --> 03:39.342
Yeah, Lily, I'd like
to show you how it's done.

03:39.344 --> 03:42.428
Billy Zabka, what
a great guy.

03:42.430 --> 03:45.314
Look at how thorough Ted was
planning the best man poker game

03:45.316 --> 03:46.849
he's throwing for Barney.

03:46.851 --> 03:49.852
Wait, I think I'm on some sort
of delay here.

03:49.854 --> 03:53.139
Best man visor
for the dealer.

03:53.141 --> 03:55.474
Customized playing cards.

03:55.476 --> 03:57.193
Barney's the king.

03:57.195 --> 03:58.611
And...

03:58.613 --> 03:59.762
the queens

03:59.764 --> 04:01.681
are naked.

04:01.683 --> 04:03.466
It was my first decree.

04:03.468 --> 04:06.686
Hmm. Plus, Ted handwrote
all of the table cards

04:06.688 --> 04:08.638
for the reception
in calligraphy.

04:08.640 --> 04:10.656
The man's a wizard
with a pen.

04:10.658 --> 04:12.925
Oh. I don't know
about all that.

04:12.927 --> 04:13.960
Though I was approached

04:13.962 --> 04:16.128
by the decorating committee
to make the...

04:16.130 --> 04:18.314
signs for our senior prom.

04:18.315 --> 04:21.817
I'm told they were
quite the hit.

04:21.819 --> 04:25.171
Hey, buddy, listen,

04:25.173 --> 04:29.125
you're gonna kill me, but I
forgot to bring the table cards.

04:29.127 --> 04:31.510
Uh, I'd hate to ask
you to redo them...

04:31.512 --> 04:33.896
Say no more.
The best man is on it.

04:33.898 --> 04:36.599
Thanks, Ted.

04:36.601 --> 04:38.701
S-So now the best man

04:38.703 --> 04:42.405
is painstakingly handwriting
200 table cards,

04:42.407 --> 04:44.857
but my maid of
honor forgot

04:44.859 --> 04:47.927
to click "send"
on an Evite.

04:47.929 --> 04:49.662
I didn't forget
to invite the girls

04:49.664 --> 04:50.997
to your bachelorette party.

04:50.999 --> 04:52.865
You have no girls!

04:52.867 --> 04:54.083
What?

04:54.085 --> 04:56.636
What?

04:56.638 --> 04:58.704
What?

04:58.706 --> 05:01.290
What? I...
All my girls.

05:01.975 --> 05:03.376
I gave you a list.

05:03.378 --> 05:04.593
This list?

05:04.595 --> 05:05.544
Yeah.

05:05.546 --> 05:07.246
"Tall girl from work,

05:07.248 --> 05:10.049
"mouth-breather
from coffee shop,

05:10.051 --> 05:11.384
"average-sized

05:11.386 --> 05:13.386
girl from that place"?

05:13.388 --> 05:15.638
Ooh. Sorry I didn't
track her down.

05:15.640 --> 05:17.039
She sounds great!

05:17.041 --> 05:19.025
She's actually
kind of a bitch.

05:19.027 --> 05:20.309
Face it, Robin.

05:20.311 --> 05:22.278
You hate women, and...

05:22.280 --> 05:24.280
women hate you.

05:25.949 --> 05:27.533
Ted didn't go to his prom?

05:27.535 --> 05:30.052
Classic.

05:30.054 --> 05:32.538
<i>While Lily was dropping the</i>
<i>ball as Robin's maid of honor,</i>

05:32.540 --> 05:35.825
<i>the best man was busy</i>
<i>knocking it out of the park.</i>

05:36.994 --> 05:39.278
Hey, buddy, listen,

05:39.280 --> 05:41.747
my great-aunt Ida has corns
on her feet

05:41.749 --> 05:43.499
and needs a first-floor room.

05:43.501 --> 05:45.334
Uh, would you mind
switching rooms?

05:45.336 --> 05:47.470
Say no more.
The best man is on it.

05:47.472 --> 05:48.554
Thanks, Ted.

